<!-- Purpose: To test the tabindex attribute used with the AREA tag -->

<!-- Expected result: Tabindex defines the position of the object in the document's tabbing sequence.  (Mac users use Command.) -->

<!-- Modified: Changed doctype to xhtml 1.0 transitional Author: Chris Petersen Date: 1/14/01 -->

<title>XHTML Functional -- AREA - TABINDEX</title>

</head>

<body>

<p>Tabindex defines the position of the object in the document's

tabbing sequence. In this case, the

tabindex will put focus on the links specified in the image.</p>

<p>Steps to take</p>

<ol>

<li> Click in the white space of the document to get focus</li>

<li>Press the tab key 5 times</li>

</ol>

<p>Result: As you tab, each colored section should be outlined in the following order:</p>

<ul>

<li>1=blue</li>

<li>2=yellow</li>

<li>3=pink</li>

<li>4=orange</li>

<li>5=lime</li>

</ul>

<img src="images/multicolor.gif" alt="multicolor" border="0" usemap="#image" width="152" height="86" /> 

<map name="image" id="image">

<area tabindex="5" shape="rect" alt="lime" coords="0,0,62,63" href="default_lime.xml" title="lime"/>

<area tabindex="3" shape="rect" alt="pink" coords="1,63,63,85" href="default_pink.xml" title="pink"/>

<area tabindex="2" shape="rect" alt="yellow" coords="63,0,87,85" href="default_yellow.xml" title="yellow"/>

<area tabindex="4" shape="rect" alt="orange" coords="88,0,150,21" href="default_orange.xml" title="orange"/>

<area tabindex="1" shape="rect" alt="blue" coords="88,21,151,85" href="default_blue.xml" title="blue"/>

</map>

</body>

